  <brief_summary>
    <textblock>
      COLEPT is a prospective interventional study that intends to better inform about&#xD;
      leptospirosis, a neglected zoonotic infectious disease. During prospective follow-up of&#xD;
      hospitalized acute leptospirosis cases, the participants will be assessed during 1 year for&#xD;
      epidemiological, clinical, bacteriological and immunological data. Main intervention consists&#xD;
      in blood sampling and biological bank constitution.&#xD;
    </textblock>
  </brief_summary>
